    "details": {
      "description": "<p>A ghostly hacker haunts their computer and attempts to drain the spirit of anyone who accessed the computer.</p>",
      "level": {
        "value": 2
      },
      "isComplex": true,
      "disable": "<p>@Check[computers|dc:16] (trained) to partition the haunted code, or @Check[religion|dc:18] (trained) or Occultism (trained) to exorcise the spirit</p>",
      "routine": "<p>(1 action) The haunt absorbs the spirits of the living, dealing @Damage[(1d10+4)[spirit]] damage to all living creatures within 10 feet of the computer (@Check[will|dc:18|basic] save). On a critical failure, a creature is additionally @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.4D2KBtexWXa6oUMR]{Drained 1}. This routine doesn't count as a hostile action for the purposes of ending the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.AdPVz7rbaVSRxHFg]{Fascinated} condition.</p>",
      "reset": "<p>The trap resets after 1 hour.</p>",
