    {
      "type": "action",
      "name": "Hacker's Fixation",
      "system": {
        "actionType": {
          "value": "reaction"
        },
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature touches the console directly or with a tool</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The haunt distracts the user with colorful graphics and interesting data while lowering their mental defenses. The triggering creature must attempt a @Check[will|dc:22] save. The trap then rolls initiative.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p><p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.e1XGnhKNSQIm5IXg]{Stupefied 1} for 1 round.</p><p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature is stupefied 1.</p><p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.e1XGnhKNSQIm5IXg]{Stupefied 2}. Additionally, they are @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.AdPVz7rbaVSRxHFg]{Fascinated} with the computer and can't take any actions except to passively view the data on the computer. At the end of each of their turns, they can retry this saving throw to remove the fascinated condition.</p>",
